metadata.name: Walk the Line
metadata.description:
I've long been obsessed with capturing human presence within the vast power of nature and the ways we choose to interact in those spaces. Within the world of outdoor enthusiasts, highliners are a special breed. Chasing their flow state, they walk a 1-inch thick line over gaps - hundreds and sometimes thousands of feet above the ground. I captured "Walk the Line" from a unique perspective, offering a full understanding of the distance to the canyon floor below.  

Location: Moab, Utah  
Highliner: Luke Hamilton
